<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Supports Modalities of OAU Framework </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia said here Thursday
that it supports the modalities of the Organization of African
Unity (OAU) framework agreement to solve the Ethio-Eritrean border
conflict.
</P>
<P>
Upon his return from Algiers, Algeria, Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi told reporters that the just-ended OAU summit had
unanimously endorsed modalities for the implementation of the OAU
framework agreement on the settlement of the dispute between the
two Horn of African neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The modalities called on Eritrea to withdraw from all Ethiopian
 territories it has occupied since May 6, 1998, the prime minister
said, adding "we feel that this is a principled and a correct
package".
</P>
<P>
The OAU framework agreement, presented to both Ethiopia and
Eritrea in November 1998, and was accepted by Ethiopia
immediately, calls for the withdrawal of Eritrean troops from all
Ethiopian territories occupied since May 6 of last year.
</P>
<P>
Also on Thursday, Ethiopian Foreign Minister Seyoum Mesfin told
a press conference here that his country would keep its commitment
to the peaceful resolution of the conflict, and once again called
on the international community to pressurize Eritrea to accept the
OAU modalities without "ifs and buts".
</P>
<P>
The war between Ethiopia and Eritrea broke out in early May of
1998 over a disputed stretch of their border. Tens of thousands
of people on both sides have been reportedly killed in the
conflict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
