<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, July 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian security forces on Wednesday discovered a
powerful bomb on the Mullah Sadra Avenue in northwestern Tehran
and defused it.
</P>
<P>
"The bomb was very powerful and could have inflicted heavy
losses if exploded," an informed source told local daily Tehran
Times published on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The source also said that the security source also discovered a
hideout used by terrorists in Tehran, but gave no details.
(BC-Iran-Bomb-Discovery)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- A U.N. technical team, which is entrusted to remove
toxic chemical agents left behind by U.N. arms inspectors, started
its work on Thursday, said a U.N. official.
</P>
<P>
Prakash Shah, U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan's representative
in Baghdad, told reporters that the U.N. team started on Thursday
to destroy the chemical agents and mustard gas samples left behind
by the U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) on disarming Iraq in its
Baghdad laboratory. (BC-Iraq-UN Team)
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus President Glafcos Clerides Thursday stressed
that a shift in Turkey's position on Cyprus would come about if
the U.N. Security Council, the G-8, Europe and others exert their
influence on Turkey.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after a commemoration service for those who
died in July 1974.
</P>
<P>
On July 15, 1974, the Greek junta, then ruling Greece,
orchestrated a coup against Cyprus president Archbishop
Makarios. Five days later, Turkish troops invaded and occupied the
northern third of the island. (BC-Cyprus-Turkey)
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus' Parliament Thursday held an extraordinary
session to denounce the military coup engineered by the Greek
military junta in July, 1974 and the Turkish invasion and
occupation that followed.
</P>
<P>
The junta toppled former president Makarios on July 15,
1974 and only five days later, Turkey invaded and occupied the
northern third of the island under the pretext of protecting the
Turkish Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
A 35,000-strong Turkish army are still stationed in the
island's northern area. (BC-Cyprus-Coup Anniversary) 
</P>
</TEXT>
