<HEADLINE> Sino-Mongolian Friendship In Common Interests, Jiang Says (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, Mongolia, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said Thursday that the sound development momentum of
Sino-Mongolian relations demonstrated that the bilateral
friendship complies with the common aspiration and fundamental
interests of their peoples.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks in an address at a banquet given by
Mongolian President Nachagyn Bagabandy in honor of the Chinese
president, who was here on a three-day state visit.
</P>
<P>
Despite some turns and twists in the bilateral relations in
the past, Jiang said that the good-neighborly friendship between
the two countries has remained the mainstream in the long river of
bilateral contacts.
</P>
<P>
Particularly after the 1990s, China-Mongolia ties witnessed
rapid recovery and growth with tangible achievements made in all
sectors, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang especially mentioned the treaty on friendship and
cooperation signed between the two countries in 1994, describing
the document as one that "laid important political and legal basis
" for the healthy growth of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state of the two countries made even more clear
the future direction of Sino-Mongolian relationship during
Bagabandy's successful China visit last December when the two
declared to build up a long-term, stable, healthy, mutually trust
relationship based on good-neighborhood, friendship and
cooperation towards the 21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The sound development momentum of bilateral ties under the
new situation proves once again the correctness of the good-
neighbor and friendly policy delineated by the two governments and
their leaders and fully demonstrates that the development of China-
Mongolian friendship meets the common aspiration and the
fundamental interests of the two peoples," Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The current Sino-Mongolian friendship is hard-earned so it
should be heartily cherished even more, he said, adding that both
countries should draw on experiences and lessons of the past half
century so as to usher in even better future for the bilateral
relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
As the new century is approaching, the two countries should
hold the common mission of advancing the bilateral friendship with
the insight of centurial perspective, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Provided the two countries are unswayed by the capricious
changes in international arena and steadfastly hold the general
direction in the bilateral development, Jiang said, it will reap
more benefits for both countries and their people, thus promoting
prosperity and development of respective nation and binding the
two as good friends and neighbors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
