<HEADLINE> Sino-Mongolian Friednship In Common Interests, Jiang Says (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Particularly when China initiated the reform and opening-up
drive some 20 years ago, the country made unprecedented progress
in all economic and social undertakings with great improvement in
both comprehensive national power and people's living standards,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people are striving to overcome obstacles in the
development path and score greater success in an effort to mark
the 50th anniversary of the founding of new China and the return
of Macao into the motherland, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang, today's world is still in the middle of
profound changes. "Even though the Cold War has ended, the
international situation is far from tranquil. The cause of peace,
which is keenly pursued and loved by peoples worldwide, still face
new challenges," he noted.
</P>
<P>
As peace lovers, the Chinese and Mongolian peoples should
adhere to each's foreign policy of peace, and together with people
of other countries, make all-out efforts to push forward the
establishment of a new, just and rational international political
and economic order, create a new world with long-lasting peace and
common prosperity, and promote the lofty humanity's cause of peace
and development, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
President Bagabandy said in his address that President Jiang's
visit, which was paid on the eve of the new century, is
significant to bring the bilateral ties into the new millennium.
Moreover, the visit is a symbolic tour for it is paid before the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The positive development of bilateral relations in the past
decade "is in the fundamental interests of both countries," he
said, adding that their cooperation witnessed marked expansion
and development in the period.
</P>
<P>
He considered the 1994 treaty played an important role in
developing the bilateral ties under the new situation. During his
previous China visit, both countries also inked several important
documents, including a joint statement in which the two nations
declared the principles for the buildup of the 21st-century-
oriented friendly and cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
He again expressed the belief that Jiang's visit will turn a
new chapter for the growth of bilateral ties and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian president said that his talks today with Jiang
was carried out in an atmosphere of sincerity, mutual
understanding and mutual respect, adding that he was satisfied
with the results of the talks.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to make concerted efforts in a bid to further
promote the long-term and steady growth of the friendly bilateral
ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bagabandy said that China's stability and development is not
only an important factor to safeguard the peace and security in
the Asia-Pacific region, but also to ensure the peace and security
for the whole world.
</P>
<P>
He in the address also expressed his congratulations to China's
achievements made in its speedy economic development, improvement
of people's life and realization of the country's prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Before the end of the banquet, Bagabandy and his wife presented
the Mongolian robes to Jiang and his wife. In return, Jiang wrote
a calligraphic work to hail the friendship between the two
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
