<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Welcomes Argentine-British Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan welcomes the agreement signed between Argentina and Britain
which provides for the resumption of air links between Argentina
and the Malvinas (Folklands), his spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Annan hails the agreement as a sign of growing goodwill and
cooperation, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The accord signed in London Wednesday by Argentine Foreign
Minister Guido Di Tella and his British counterpart, Robin Cook,
paved the way for the resumption of air flights cut off since the
1982 war for the sovereignty of the islands.
</P>
<P>
Argentine President Carlos Menem said the direct flight from
Argentina will take off on October 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
