<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.6 on
the Richter scale rocked Cyprus' capital Nicosia and the coastal
towns of Paphos and Limassol at 17:45 (14:45 GMT) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
No casualties or damages have been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
According to Cyprus' Geological Department, the epicenter of
the quake, the third in two months, was in the sea, some 40
kilometers southwest of Paphos.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus is classified as a seismically active zone, but is not
among those countries that are considered high risk earthquake
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
