<HEADLINE> Greece Willing to Mediate For Power Transition in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Greece Thursday expressed its
willingness to support a proposal for the formation of a
transitional government in Yugoslavia, put forward by the leader
of the Serbian Renewal Party, Vuk Draskovic, who is now in Athens
for visist.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after his talks with Draskovic, Greek Foreign Minister
George Papandreou said that the Greek government was willing to
back this prospect and mediate with Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic in order to make possible a smooth power transition.
</P>
<P>
Draskovic proposed the replacement of Milosevic with a
political figure belonging to the party of Milo Djukanovic,
president of Montenegro, one of Yugoslavia's two federated
republics. 
</P>
