<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Telecom to Buy 10 Percent of British Cable TV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The French telecommunications
company, France Telecom, will buy 10 percent of the shares of the
British cable TV company NTL with 1 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The director in charge of finance affairs of France Telecom,
Jean-Louis Vincigerra, said that once allied with France Telecom,
the NTL will be an alternative to the historical operator BT and
paid TV network BSkyB in the fields of paid TV programs, internet
service, advertisement and electronic business.
</P>
<P>
The NTL, which covers the whole territory of the United Kingdom
in cable TV, internet and fixed telephone service, is in the
process of allying with another British cable TV network, the
Cable and Wireless Communications, which will result in a sharing
of half the cable TV market in the UK.
</P>
<P>
The third British cable TV network, the Telewest, could also be
drawn into a future alliance, said France Telecom officials.
</P>
<P>
France Telecom has set up an alliance with Deutsche Telecom in
Germany, but it is very weak in the British telecommunications
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
