<HEADLINE> China to Provide Financial Assistance for Fifth Friendship Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China will provide financial
assistance to Bangladesh for the construction of the fifth
Bangladesh-China Friendship Bridge over River Gabkhan on
Barishal-Jhalakathi-Bhandaria-Pirojpur road in the southwestern
part of the South Asian nation.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect was signed here Thursday between M.
A. Wadud, chief engineer of the Road and Highway Directorate, and
Gao Yongwen, president of China's Heilongjiang International
Economic and Technical Cooperative Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Communications Minister Anwar Hossain Manju and Chinese
Ambassador to Bangladesh Wang Chungui were present at the signing
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the 918-meter-long and 10-meter-wide bridge
will begin on September 1.
</P>
<P>
The decision on the construction of the bridge was made during
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's visit to China in 1996, according
to the communications minister. 
</P>
