<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Russia to Establish Joint Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian President Negaso
Gidada met Russian ambassador Vladmir Volkov here Thursday. The
two sides agreed to establish a joint commission to promote
bilateral relations, a spokesman for the Ethiopian Foreign
Ministry has said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have agreed to hold a conference in Moscow,
Russia in August this year to establish the joint commission, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Negaso described the decision to set up the commission as
"appropriate and timely".
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the existing bilateral relations
between Addis Ababa and Moscow would further be consolidated.
</P>
<P>
A Russian delegation headed by Deputy Trade Minister Vladimir
Pakhomov visited Ethiopia in early May this year, during which
officials of Russia and Ethiopia signed agreed minutes to further
streamline their economic and technical cooperations. 
