<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Sportsmen to Compete at All African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-four Ethiopian athletes
will compete in five sports disciplines at the 7th All African
Games due to be held in Johannesburg, South Africa in September
this year, a senior Ethiopian official has revealed.
</P>
<P>
Athletics, boxing, table tennis, weight-lifting and cycling are
the five disciplines to represent Ethiopia at the Games, Sports
News quoted Ato Solomon Bekele, secretary of the Ethiopian
National Games Preparation Committee, as saying Thursday.
</P>
