<HEADLINE> Dierckxsens Wins 11th Stage, Armstrong Keeps Jersey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Ludo Dierckxsens of Belgium won
Thursday's 11th stage of the Tour de France cycling race from
Bourg d'Oisans to Saint-Etienne of France, while American Lance
Armstrong kept leader's jersey.
</P>
<P>
Dierckxsens sprinted to home in four hours 34 minutes and three
seconds, a minute and a half ahead of the rest of the five-man
leading group.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Dimitri Konyshev came in second while Kazakhstan's
Alexandre Vinokourov in third in the 198.5 kilometers Alpine ride.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong now leads by seven minutes and 42 seconds from
Abraham Olano of Spain. 
