<HEADLINE> France Calls on EU to Keep Vigilance on British Beef </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- France called on the European Union
(EU) Thursday to keep "the biggest vigilance" on British beef
after the EU partially lifted its embargo on British beef exports.
</P>
<P>
"The French government stressed the absolute priority which
should be given to the principle of precaution," said French
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
She said that France wants the EU Commission to make sure about
a good implementation of the commitment made by the United
Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
"The French government has taken note of the decision of the EU
Commission authorizing the partial resumption of the exports of
British beef from August 1st, with the indications according to
which all the conditions and guarantees have been met to this
effect," said the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
France discovered this week two new cases of bovine spongiform
encephalopathy, also called mad cow disease.
</P>
<P>
The EU Commission has lifted a three-year embargo on British
beef exports, which was imposed after the outbreak of the mad cow
disease.
</P>
<P>
The EU maintains its ban on exports of living cows by Britain.
</P>
</TEXT>
