<HEADLINE> Nepali Children to Be Vaccinated Against Japanese Encephalitis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Some 170,000 Nepali children
aged from one to 15 will be vaccinated against Japanese
encephalitis on July 18 through 24, the official RSS news agency
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The vaccination program will be first conducted in Bardia
district, one of the 24 districts in the Terai region mostly
affected by the disease.
</P>
<P>
In the region in southern Nepal, about 10,000 people are
affected by the disease and 500 to 1,000 of them have died.
</P>
<P>
The vaccination program will be extended to other affected
districts, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Vaccination is said to be very effective and safe in the
present context when good treatment of the disease is not
available. 
