messenger of the people of Israel who have called for change and
renewal."
</P>
<P>
"I am determined to bring about change and renewal," he said.
</P>
<P>
Barak said he would "inject new momentum into the peace process
and to put it back on all tracks."
</P>
<P>
"It is our intention to inject new momentum into the peace
process and to put it back on all tracks," he said. "For this we
need American leadership and support all along the way."
</P>
<P>
He said the United States could contribute to the process "more
as a facilitator than as a kind of policeman, judge and arbitrator
at the same time."
</P>
<P>
Barak said he hoped his visit will "usher in a new era in the
peace process and further deepen American-Israeli relations."
</P>
<P>
Clinton, referring to the U.S. role in the peace process, said
the United States "has no business trying to prejudge the final
status issues."
</P>
<P>
Barak said Israel would live up to all agreements, including
last October's Wye agreement on Israel's further pullback in the
West Bank. He also promised to pursue agreements with with Syria
and Lebanon, and he said he was prepared to meet with Syrian
President Hafez Assad. "It takes two to tango. I am ready," he
said. 
</P>
