<HEADLINE> Angola to Implement "Emergency Strategy" on War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of Angola's
Council of Ministers decided Thursday at a meeting that the
country will implement an "emergency strategy" to resolve the
problem of war refugees which have reached over 1.7 million in the
southern African country.
</P>
<P>
A press communique issued here Thursday by the meeting said
given the remarkably reducing relief goods from the international
community, and the limited fund on the part of the government, the
Angolan authorities decided to turn the previous direct relief
into self-relief through production by the refugees themselves.
</P>
<P>
Since July of this year, the government has set aside a special
fund for the purchase of seeds, farm tools and other means of
production and distributed them through credit financing to ensure
the basic needs of refugees.
</P>
<P>
The number of refugees in the country increased sharply
following the renewed civil war late last year. More than 400,000
refugees were concentrated in Huambo and Kuito cities in central
Angola and Malanje city in the north which have long been besieged
by the rebel National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The United Nations, however, could only come forth with half of
the food aid it promised due to the refugee problem in Kosovo and
worsening security situation in Angola which makes relief work
difficult.
</P>
<P>
The U.N.-pledged aid, if materialized, could only meet the
needs of 49 percent of the Angolan refugees, which is far from the
demand termed by the Angolan government as "on the verge of a
humanitarian crisis".

NNNN
04:11 04:11 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
