<HEADLINE> Lukashenko: U.S. Assumes Constructive Position on Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian President Alexander
Lukashenko said Thursday that the United States has already
assumed a constructive position on Belarus.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting in Minsk with Adrian Severin, leader of the
working group for Belarus of the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe's Parliamentary Assembly, Lukashenko said
Belarus welcomes the latest contacts with the European
organizations and with the United States, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Such contacts were aimed at preserving peace and stability in
Belarus, he said.
</P>
<P>
