<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Mongolian Parliament Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, Mongolia, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here Friday afternoon that the world should be a
multi-polar one for no single management pattern can be applicable
universally.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during his meeting with Chairman of the
Mongolian State Great Hural Radnaasumberel Gonchigdorj.
</P>
<P>
He said that the world has about 200 countries and 2,500 ethnic
groups. "Every country hopes to realize development amidst
stability while keeping its own features," he noted.
</P>
<P>
