anniversary of the forging of diplomatic ties between China and
Mongolia and the fifth anniversary of the signing of a bilateral
treaty on friendship and cooperation, Jiang extended his gratitude
to the hospitality of the Mongolian people and hoped his visit
could further promote the mutual understanding and trust, as well
as the friendship and cooperation between the two countries and
peoples.
</P>
<P>
Gonchigdorj told Jiang that the inter-parliament contacts
constituted an important part of state-to-state relations.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the State Great Hural expanded its relations
with China's National People's Congress (NPC), he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reiterated that China has always attached importance to
its ties with Mongolia, saying that the bilateral friendship has
been deeply rooted in the hearts of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
When the new century is approaching, China will make concerted
efforts with the Mongolian side to build up an even better China-
Mongolia relationship based on the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence and in line with the spirit of the 1994 treaty signed
between the two countries, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang believed that the exchanges between NPC and the Great
Hural have further deepened the understanding of the two peoples
and enhanced the friendly cooperation between the two legislatures.
</P>
<P>
For that, he gave positive remarks to the efforts made by
Gonchigdorj and the Mongolian parliament.
</P>
<P>
Jiang hoped the two sides to carry out ever frequent and
fruitful exchanges in a bid to strengthen and develop the China-
Mongolia good-neighborly friendship. 
</P>
