<HEADLINE> Fujian Remaining Center of Action Against Attempts to Divide China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The eastern China province of
Fujian, which is just opposite the island of Taiwan, will continue
to abide by the basic "one country, two systems" principle as an
essential center for China's peaceful unification.
</P>
<P>
This statement came today at a seminar of the province's Taiwan
Affairs Office and the Taiwan Studies Society of Fujian in Fuzhou,
the provincial capital. Members of the two organizations and those
of the Fujian Academy of Social Sciences participated in the
seminar and criticized Taiwan's Lee Teng-hui for his separatism.
</P>
<P>
Yang Yanjie, a deputy head of the academy's Taiwan Studies
Institute, pointed out that Lee's remark about "two states" was a
new obstacle in the path to peaceful unification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Jianfeng, a deputy head of the academy's Asia Pacific
Research Institute, said that Lee has seriously damaged the
interests of the people of Taiwan, destabilized the cross-Straits
situation, and jeopardized China's peaceful unification.
</P>
<P>
Xu Xiaokang, of the Taiwan Studies Society, said that cross-
Straits economic cooperation should not be affected by political
problems and that exchanges and contacts between people across the
Taiwan Straits should be promoted to jointly develop the culture
of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Weng Zhiguang, an associate research fellow at the academy,
said that as an important base for the peaceful unification of the
motherland, Fujian will continue to carry out the basic principle
of peaceful unification and the "one country, two systems"
principle and that the province is against any malice caused by
the attempt to split China into "two Chinas" or "one China, one
Taiwan".  
</P>
</TEXT>
