<HEADLINE> Malaysian Stocks Close Lower on Profit-taking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) finished slightly lower Friday, due
mostly to profit-taking activity.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Index (CI) eased 1.74 points to 843.12.
</P>
<P>
The broader Emas Index shed 2.34 points to 222.86, while the
Industrial Index slipped 1.92 points to 1,474.10.
</P>
<P>
Leading the downtrend was the Finance Index which dipped 81.66
points to 6,689.15.
</P>
<P>
Losing counters outnumbered gainers 494 to 259, while 86
counters were unchanged, 77 untraded and 12 others suspended.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover for the day remained strong at 1.26 billion
shares valued at 2.944 billion ringgit (775 million U.S. dollars).
Thursday's volume stood at 1.499 billion shares valued at 3.14
billion ringgit (826 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Volume on the Main Board narrowed slightly to 1.192 billion
shares at 2.76 billion ringgit (726 million dollars) from 1.45
billion shares valued at 3.0 billion ringgit (789 million dollars)
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Second Board turnover, however, rose to 69.08 million shares
worth 179.68 million ringgit (47.3 million dollars) from 47.56
million shares at 123.68 million ringgit (32.5 million dollars)
previously.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals plunged to 16.61 million shares worth 59.39
million ringgit (15.6 million dollars) from 87.63 million shares
valued at 102.52 million (26.98 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
A dealer said the market remained impassive to the announcement
by the Statistics Department on Malaysia's manufacturing sales
revealing a rise of 14.7 percent to 20.3 billion ringgit (5.34
billion dollars) in May from 17.7 billion ringgit (4.66 billion
dollars) in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
On the Malaysian Exchange of Securities Dealing and Automated
Quotation, the Mesdaq Composite Index (MCI) ended unchanged at
100.63. 
</P>
</TEXT>
