<HEADLINE> New Flood Peak Expected on Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A new flood peak is building on the
Yangtze River as a result of torrential rains in most parts of the
upper and middle reaches.
</P>
<P>
The Wujiang and Jialing rivers and areas around the Three
Gorges and Dongting Lake have all had large amounts of
precipitation since Thursday, according to the Yangtze River Water
Conservation Committee.
</P>
<P>
Floodwaters caused by torrential rains have already formed in
the Three Gorges area and water levels at monitoring stations
along the main stream of the river have all risen and analysts are
predicting that, by July 20th, the discharge rate could reach 50,
000 cubic meters per second at Yichang in Hubei Province and that
a third peak could form by then.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains are still expected on many areas along the Yangtze
over the next three to five days, which will mean greater pressure
on flood prevention efforts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
