<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Commentator Says Dividing Motherland Is  Historical Sin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Lee Teng-hui has made himself a
sinner in history by attempting to split the motherland when he
redefined the cross-Straits relations as "state-to-state",
according to a Xinhua commentator.
</P>
<P>
Lee gradually tore off his camouflage and changed his policy
towards the mainland from the "one China" principle. According to
reports from Taiwan, on July 9, he said that the cross-Straits
relations should be "state-to-state or at least special state-to-
state relations".
</P>
<P>
The Xinhua commentator says that Lee was trying to take
advantage of current situation in the United States, where there
has been a series of anti-China farces and he deliberately chose a
German radio station to speak out, hinting that the cross-Straits
relations were like the two Germanys.
</P>
<P>
But Lee's efforts are fruitless, the commentator says, because
relations across the Taiwan Straits have never been like those of
the two Germanys. His devisive remarks also exposed his attempt to
impose his influence on Taiwan's political situation when he
leaves office next year.
</P>
<P>
The cross-Straits relations climate has improved since last
year with the joint effort of the Chinese everywhere, it says,
adding Taiwan compatriots have expressed the hope that cross-
Straits dialogues can continue and they are looking forward to
Wang Daohan's visit to Taiwan later this year.
</P>
<P>
The progress in cross-Straits relations runs against Lee's
original idea, the commentator noted. His remark was designed to
further undermine the 'one-China' principle -- the foundation for
the cross-Straits contacts, dialogues and negotiations -- and to
wreck the peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
There is only one China in the world and Taiwan is an
inalienable part of the country, it goes on, stressing that
separation of China's territorial integrity and sovereignty is not
allowed.
</P>
<P>
There is no way out for Lee's divisiveness and he is doomed to
failure. The commentator cautions Lee's followers to consider the
long-term interests of Taiwan compatriots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
