<HEADLINE> Marathon Runner Pippig Suspended for Drug Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- German marathon runner Uta Pippig has
been suspended for two years for doping, a German athletics
official said on Friday in Darmstadt, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Pippig, three-time winner of the women's race in the Boston
Marathon, will miss next year's Sydney Olympics after the judicial
commission of the German Athletics Federation imposed the
suspension on the star.
</P>
<P>
Commission president Wolfgang Schoppe confirmed the federation'
s initial decision, which was carried out last October after
Pippig failed a drug test. 
</P>
