<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Opens Investment Guide on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- An investment guide to
Ethiopia which provides a listing of specific investment
opportunities in the country, has been posted on the Internet, the
Ethiopian Investment Authority announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The guide, prepared with the support of the United Nations
Conferences on Trade and Development and the International Chamber
of Commerce, gives " a broad overview of the current investment
opportunities and prevailing socio-economic and political
conditions", said the Ethiopian investment authority.
</P>
<P>
In addition to lists of current investors and areas of
investment in the Horn of Africa country, the guide also gives
"general guidance on the necessary legal and other issues related
to undertaking investment in Ethiopia."
</P>
<P>
Over the period between 1992/93 and 1998/99, the investment
authority approved 163 foreign investment projects, of which 21
have become operational and 49 are under implementation.
</P>
<P>
The projects include a five-star hotel, a major brewery, a
shoe- manufacturing plant and investments in edible oils and
bottling.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has been trying to absorb foreign investment to speed
up national development, particularly in the sectors of
manufacturing, agriculture, real estate development, education,
health and mining.
</P>
<P>
Italy, Britain, France, Germany, Saudi Arabia, South Korea and
the United States are currently the main sources of foreign
investment in Ethiopia, according to the investment authority.
</P>
</TEXT>
