<HEADLINE> Palestinian Problem Has to Be Solved First: Turkish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel,
who is currently visiting Palestine, Friday emphasized the
importance of the Palestine problem, saying it has to be solved
first.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a joint news conference with the Palestinian
Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat, following bilateral talks in
Gaza, Demirel also said that the region is experiencing a "golden
opportunity" for the resolution of the Arab-Israeli dispute, and
that all parties should benefit.
</P>
<P>
Demirel added that the Palestine problem constituted the core
of the conflict and should, therefore, be resolved first in order
to establish lasting and comprehensive peace.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Turkey would also welcome any agreements
between Israel and Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Demirel came to Gaza from Jerusalem where he paied a two-day
visit and had talks with Israeli leaders. He is expected to
conclude his stay here later Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is one of the countries that has committed itself to
financial aid to the Palestinian self-rule area. It has promised
to provide 54 million U.S. dollars to the Palestinians and about 4
million dollars have already been put in place. 
</P>
