<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Appoint Defense Forces Deputy Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Defense Minister
General Wiranto Friday confirmed that Admiral Widodo, now the
Indonesian naval chief of staff, is slated to assume the position
of deputy commander of the National Defense Forces (TNI).
</P>
<P>
President B.J. Habibie is scheduled to install Widodo at the
State Palace Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the reinstitution of the TNI deputy commander job
had something to do with the coming general session of the
People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), which will elect a new
president and vice president, Wiranto emphatically said: "That is
too far-fetched."
</P>
<P>
"This is a matter of professionalism. It has nothing to do with
politics," said Wiranto who is also commander of the TNI.
</P>
<P>
Rumors have it that the creation of the post of deputy TNI
commander is part of the effort to pave the way for Wiranto's
nomination for vice presidency.
</P>
<P>
According to Wiranto, the appointment of the TNI deputy
commander was meant to step up the military's effectiveness in
safeguarding national integrity and territory.
</P>
<P>
"That is why I proposed that the TNI deputy commander post be
filled by a navy officer," Wiranto said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
