<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Enjoys Steady Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China's agricultural sector
experienced steady growth momentum in the first half this year,
reaping bumper harvests of summer crops and oil seeds and
increasing output of aquatic and orchard products.
</P>
<P>
Ye Zhen, spokesman of the National Bureau of Statistics, told a
press conference here today that primary industries, predominately
agriculture, had a 3-percent growth rate year-on-year during the
first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
He said that summer grain crops were over five million tons
more than a year earlier, and the output of oil-seeds crops is
expected to increase by more than 1.4 million tons, or 15 percent
year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
During the January-June period, the Chinese government
increased investment in agriculture and water conservancy by 76.8
percent over a year ago, and the ratio of agricultural investment
to total fixed assets investment increased by 1.5 percentage
points on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
According to Ye, the rural market saw steady growth during the
period, with retail sales of consumer goods rising by 6.2 percent
year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that by the end of May, restructuring of
the crop mix had helped reduce the planting area of cotton by 542,
000 hectares from last year, down to 3.47 million hectares this
year.
</P>
<P>
He said that the price of pork continued to drop for the past
six months due to an oversupplied market, and explained that the
fluctuation of pork prices is a normal phenomenon of market
competition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
