<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Adopt New  Foreign Exchange Management Measures(1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China will adopt a series of new
measures to improve its foreign exchange management with a view to
encouraging exports and the utilization of overseas investment, a
senior foreign exchange official told a national conference which
closed here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the national conference on foreign exchange,
exports, and overseas investments jointly organized by the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) and
the State Administration of Foreign Exchange (SAFE), Lu Nanping,
deputy director of SAFE, said "these measures will help encourage
exports and the inflow of overseas capital."
</P>
<P>
"We will also make sure that relevant foreign trade companies
operate according to law and no loss of foreign exchange occurs,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The measures SAFE has already taken and will adopt include:
</P>
<P>
-- Ceasing the examination and verification of the surrender of
export receipts and entry to improve the efficiency of capital;
</P>
<P>
-- Preferential treatment for "honorable enterprises for export
receipts" in collection of export-receipt assessment to cut costs;
</P>
<P>
-- Easing restrictions on yuan loans under external
hypothecation and external guarantees;
</P>
</TEXT>
