<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rebels Kill 50 Innocent Civilians in C. Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan rebel UNITA troops
killed some 50 innocent women and children at a village in central
Huambo Tuesday, the official Journal of Angola newspaper reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted eyewitnesses as saying that at the village of
Sachitembo, troops of the National Union for Total Independence of
Angola launched a sudden attack on the market of the village.
</P>
<P>
Many women bringing with them their children were buying and
selling things at the market when the UNITA troops launched
attack. They forced the women and children to gather together,
and then shot with assault rifles in very short distance.
</P>
<P>
After the killing, most of the villagers were forced to flee
into the forest nearby.
</P>
<P>
The UNITA forces have been launching sneak attacks on innocent
people to create a wave of refugees and exert political and social
pressure upon the Angolan government in a bid to delay the
destructive hit from the army, Governor of Huambo Province Paulo
Cassamas said recently.
</P>
<P>
In the past two months, the number of refugees in the
provincial city of Huambo has soared up to 230,000 from previously
172,000, the governor noted.
</P>
<P>
Despite constant attacks by the rebels, the Angolan government
troops are controlling the general situation of the country,
another senior official said earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Deputy Minister of Defense Armado Cruz Neto disclosed
that the government troops have advanced at several front lines,
citing the successful operation in the town of Sanza Pombo in
northern Uige Province and the central city of Huambo.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government said repeatedly that it would launch a
large- scale offensive during the dry season so as to wipe out the
military forces of the UNITA led by Jonas Savimbi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
