<HEADLINE> China to Adopt New Foreign Exchange Management Measures (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Simplifying the procedure for sale and payment of foreign
exchange for foreign-invested companies when they import
technology;
</P>
<P>
-- Canceling the ban on foreign-invested company's changing
settlement accounts into fixed deposit accounts; and
</P>
<P>
-- Giving the power of examination and approval of foreign
exchange surrendering under current account and the power of
approval on repayment of the principle and payment of interest
under external debts, of all companies, including the foreign-
invested, to lower levels of management.
</P>
<P>
The deputy director said SAFE will strengthen coordination with
MOFTEC and exchange information constantly concerning strikes
against foreign exchange fraud, illegal arbitrage of foreign
exchange, and foreign exchange evasion.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 officials from foreign trade and foreign exchange
departments of central and local governments and foreign trade
companies made assessments of these measures and offered their
suggestions for revisions during the two-day conference.
</P>
<P>
Sun Zhenyu, MOFTEC vice-minister, urged local trade and foreign
exchange officials at the meeting to implement the measures and
simplify procedures on foreign exchange in order to create a
better business environment.  
</P>
