<HEADLINE> US Insurer Invests More in Chinese Privately Owned Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- John Hancock Mutual Life Insurance
Company of the United States has committed 15 million U.S. dollars
to its China investment portfolio.
</P>
<P>
John Hancock made the commitment to ChinaVest V.L.P., a limited
partnership which will invest in enterprising private companies
that are expanding in China, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Derek Chilvers, chairman and chief executive officer of John
Hancock International Holdings, Inc. said that John Hancock's
investment will help provide private businesses with the capital
they need to expand into larger organizations with independent,
professional management and a corporate structure.
</P>
<P>
Until now, John Hancock's investment have been in the
infrastructure sector, specifically transportation, water
resources, and power, he said. This new commitment expands John
Hancock's involvement into the private manufacturing and consumer
products sector.
</P>
<P>
He added that "we believe that China has a brilliant future and
we will expand our portfolio of China investment."
</P>
<P>
John Hancock is one of the world's largest life insurance
companies with over 126 billion U.S. dollars in assets under
management and 137 years of experience.  
</P>
