<HEADLINE> Team USA Runs to Rout of Uruguay in Pre-Olympic Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 16 (Xinhua) -- After a season of stagnant
offense, the NBA stars on Team USA showed Uruguay they can still
run and gun.
</P>
<P>
With a furious fast-break offense and tenacious trapping
defense, Team USA routed Uruguay 118-72, Thursday night in its
opener in the Pre-Olympic qualifying tournament of the Americas in
San Juan, Puerto Rico.
</P>
<P>
As expected, the heavily favored Americans never trailed and
were far too much for Uruguay, which was coming off an overtime
upset of Cuba on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Seattle SuperSonics guard Gary Payton scored 15 of his 20
points in the first half, when Team USA used a 31-0 edge in fast-
break points and a 20-0 advantage in points off turnovers to build
a 62-28 lead.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the Americans shot 66 percent (53-of-80), including a
blistering 80 percent (44-of-55) inside the 3-point arc. They
forced 25 turnovers and made 17 steals.
</P>
<P>
Minnesota Timberwolves forward Kevin Garnett scored 20 points
on 10-of-12 shooting and Phoenix Suns guard Jason Kidd handed out
14 assists for Team USA, which has never lost with NBA players in
international competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
