<HEADLINE> China Ocean Shipping Shows Steady Half-Year Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The China Ocean Shipping
Corporation (COSCO) said today that it had achieved steady growth
in the first six months this year.
</P>
<P>
According to Sun Jiakang, a company spokesman, COSCO handled 64.
2 million tons of goods in the January-June period, a rise of 14
percent on an annual basis. This included 1.78 million TEUs
handled by the company's container shipping branch, which was a 9.
2-percent increase.
</P>
<P>
COSCO's bulk cargo shipping branch accounted for 15.88 million
tons, an annual growth of 40.7 percent, but the branch for sundry
cargo shipping sustained a drop of 5.6 percent, handling 5.6
million tons in the past six months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
