<HEADLINE> HK LegCo Approves Amendment to Immigration Ordinance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Legislative Council (LegCo)
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Friday
approved a resolution moved by Regina Ip, secretary for security,
for some technical amendments to the Immigration Ordinance.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, with an amendment to it by Secretary for
Justice Elsie Leung, was approved with 35 from the 57 members
present voting for, 20 against and 1 abstention.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before the LegCo, Ip said she moved to amend the
wording of some articles of the Immigration Ordinance to avoid any
doubts from members of the public about the ordinance after the
interpretation by the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress of China to parts of the Basic Law following the verdict
of the Court of Final Appeal of the HKSAR about the right of abode
for children born in China's mainland to residents of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
After the approval of the resolution, the application for
settlement in Hong Kong by children of Hong Kong permanent
residents in the mainland will resume, Ip said.
</P>
<P>
In this session of the LegCo general meeting, which began
Wednesday, ordinances about the development of Chinese medicine in
Hong Kong and the arrangement for the scheduled LegCo election in
the year 2000 were also passed.
</P>
<P>
After this session, the Legislative Council will adjourn its
general meeting till October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
