<HEADLINE> Siemens Opens Representative Office in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Siemens (China) Co., Ltd.
established today its first representative office in Changsha,
capital of Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Since the implementation of the reforms and opening-up in the
1980s, Siemens has provided the province with various products and
systems, especially for industry, communications, energy, medical
engineering, and transportation, according to the company's
president.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Changsha office will help the company search
for investment opportunities in Hunan and help introduce
technology to the central China province and neighboring areas.
</P>
<P>
Siemens provided the first telephone exchange for Changsha in
1987 and now the total capacity of Siemens exchanges operating in
the city has reached two million lines, nearly half of the local
market.
</P>
<P>
Siemens has established 12 solely-funded companies and 43 joint
ventures in China. The Changsha office is the 23rd of its kind in
China.  
