<HEADLINE> China's Leading Steel Company Donates to Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Capital Iron and Steel Group,
an industrial giant also known as Shougang Group, donated one
million yuan today to help poverty-stricken students resume their
schooling.
</P>
<P>
The donation is being given to the famous "Hongzhi Class," a
special education unit at the Guangqumen Middle School in Beijing
for local children who are excellent students but from poor
families.
</P>
<P>
Wang Wenjuan, a senior high-school student from the class, said
that her mother lost her job and couldn't afford the tuition fee.
</P>
<P>
Wang expressed her gratitude for the financial aid, saying, "I
have a chance to return to school, and I will take the chance and
work hard."
</P>
<P>
Bi Qun, president of the 80-year-old steel company, said the
enterprise has always regarded supporting the country's
educational development as its obligation.
</P>
<P>
The Hongzhi Class has been opened for four years and has
provided 186 poor students with the opportunity to continue their
education, said Li Jinhai, principal of the middle school.
</P>
<P>
The donation will be used for school tuition and materials,
school uniform, and lodging. At the same time, outstanding
students in the class will receive allowances and scholarships.
</P>
</TEXT>
