<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed weaker on
the Singapore Stock Market Friday with the benchmark Straits Times
Index (STI) losing 25.21 points to close at 2,132.51 points.
</P>
<P>
The volume totaled 681.35 million shares valued at 780.74
million Singapore dollars (about 458.82 million U.S. dollars).
Losers outstripped gainers by 336 to 35 with 74 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hotung was the most heavily traded stock with a turnover of
48.47 million shares. It was followed by AFP that had 45.23
million units done. GoldenAg was the next with 25.68 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH 100 led the gainers of the day shooting up 220 cents to
close at 35.00 Singapore dollars. SPH climbed up 160 cents to
finish at 34.20 Singapore dollars. Goodwood edged up 100 cents to
end at 26.00 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS and DBS F headed the descent losing 110
cents each to finish at 16.10 and 18.60 Singapore dollars
respectively. Bukit Sem and GE Life sank 60 cents each to close at
7.30 and 22.30 Singapore dollars respectively. Seaview retreated
50 cents to end at 8.00 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the government's revision of first quarter
GDP to 0.8 percent from 1.2 percent due to a change in statistical
methodology continued to weigh on the market. 
</P>
