mob damaged offices of the ruling party at Mtoni area in Dar es
Salaam, and threw stone at cars and broke window screens, which
caused a loss of one million shillings (about 1,350 U.S. dollars).
 A policeman was injured during the scuffle.
</P>
<P>
Candidates of the ruling party won the parliamentary
by-elections for the Ubungo and Temeke constituencies in the
capital city held last Sunday by narrow margins.
</P>
<P>
In Ubungo, former Deputy Finance Minister Venance Ngula scooped
23,790 votes, beating his nearest rival Hussein Mmassy of the
opposition party, who managed to get 21,530 votes. In Temeke,
John Kibasso of the ruling party defeated Tambwe Hizza of the
opposition party by 27,090 to 25,742.
