<HEADLINE> China's Urban Air Quality Remains Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Most of China's cities had stable
air quality this week. The air-pollution index was rising, however,
in Xi'an and Guangzhou, according to the weekly air-quality report
released today by the China Environment Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
This week, among the 46 major monitored cities, Xi'an,
Guangzhou, and Urumqi reported slight air pollution; 27 cities
including Beijing, Jinan, Hohhot and Lanzhou enjoyed good air
quality, and the other 16 cities including Hefei, Zhanjiang, and
Changsha reported excellent air quality.
</P>
<P>
The major pollutant in Beijing, Guangzhou, and Shanghai is
nitrogen dioxide; in Xi'an, Jinan, and Urumqi, it is suspended
particles; and in Chongqing and Guiyang, sulfur dioxide is the
chief pollutant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
