<HEADLINE> Beer Sales to Exceed 20 Million Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Beer sales are expected to exceed
20 million tons in China this year, Du lujun, general secretary of
the China Beer Association said here today.
</P>
<P>
 China's beer industry has greatly expanded its scale of
production over the past several years, and more beer enterprises
brewing quality products are growing into giant corporations.
</P>
<P>
 According to Du, Beijing is the largest beer market, and
Yanjing Beer currently sells best in China with annual sales
exceeding 800,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
 China has been the world's second largest beer producer and
provider since 1993, and sales will surely surpass 20 million tons
this year, she said.
</P>
<P>
 Specialists in the industry are urging domestic beer
producers to enhance quality and come up with new products
suitable for a variety of consumption levels.  
</P>
