<HEADLINE> Egyptian Woman Rescued After Months of Confinement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A young woman has been rescued by
the police in southern Egypt after her father tried to kill her by
locking her in a tiny room for more than three months, the
Egyptian Gazette newspaper reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The police found Madiha Eid Ali, 23, on Wednesday while
searching for weapons in a house next to her parents' home in the
town of Akhmim, 340 kilometers south of Cairo, and heard Eid Ali
crying for help, the English-language newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Eid Ali told the police that her father, Abdu Ali, got angry
with her after her 80-year-old husband divorced her under pressure
from his children. She said she had married to escape her father
and stepmother's home.
</P>
<P>
Abdu Ali locked his daughter in a windowless one-square-meter
room for 108 days, the police said, adding that Eid Ali was found
weak and frail. She has been hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
The woman accused her father of confining her without food, but
said her younger brother, Mustafa, had smuggled water and bread to
her from time to time, the police said.
</P>
<P>
Abdu Ali fled after he heard of his daughter's rescue. The
police said they were searching for the man. 
</P>
</TEXT>
