<HEADLINE> China to Use New Foreign Exchange Exit Permit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The State Administration of
Foreign Exchange (SAFE) and the General Administration of Customs
today issued a joint circular proclaiming that new certificates
will be used for the exit of foreign exchange starting on August 1,
and that the existing certificates will become invalid on
September 1.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the SAFE said that the new certificates will
standardize Customs administration of foreign exchange and crack
down on illegal foreign exchange practices and smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman gave assurances that this move will not affect
individuals who carry foreign exchange in cash.
</P>
<P>
The circular gives detailed procedures for applying for the new
certificates.  
