<HEADLINE> Computer Festival Opens In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A ten-day computer festival opened
today in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Exhibitions of computer hardware, software, and electronic
publications will be presented, together with a seminar on
cooperation and market development among computer manufacturers,
software developers, and electronic publishers.
</P>
<P>
The festival is sponsored by the General Publishing House and
the Xinhua Bookstore Group in the province, as well as a hi-tech
development service company in Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
This is the first such exhibition ever held in China jointly
sponsored by computer products manufacturers and publishers, and
comes in response to the booming popularity of computers in the
country.
</P>
<P>
There will be some 40 domestic computer-related companies
including Great Wall and Founder participating in the exhibition.
</P>
</TEXT>
