<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Global Storage Management Software Market to Expand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The global market for storage
management software is expected to expand from 2.6 billion U.S.
dollars in 1998 to over 6.6 billion dollars in 2003, according to
a U.S. report released Thursday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. market research firm Dataquest said in its report that
storage area networks (SAN), intelligent storage servers and new
data replication techniques will revolutionize the way storage
backup and recovery is accomplished, providing consistent,
integrated and automated tools for the resulting storage
management environment.
</P>
<P>
Storage management refers to the administration of any or all
backing, archival disaster recovery and hierarchical storage
management procedures within an organization.
</P>
<P>
Dataquest divides the storage management market into three
major segments: storage infrastructure products, data management
products and enterprise storage resource management products.
</P>
<P>
Storage infrastructure products provide basic data organization
functions such as file systems, volume management and physical
replication to ensure data integrity and availability by offering
fast failure recovery and data redundancy. The market reached 626
million dollars in 1998 and is expected to hit 1.9 billion dollars
by 2003.
</P>
<P>
Data management products include backup, restore, archive and
hierarchical storage management tools. As a leading factor driving
the worldwide storage management software market, this segment
accounted for nearly 1.6 billion dollars in 1998 and is expected
to reach 3 billion dollars by 2003.
</P>
<P>
Enterprise storage resource management products provide
management of various storage resources on the network, including
magnetic disk, tape and optical media. This segment is projected
to show the strongest growth, from 382 million dollars in 1998 to
1.7 billion dollars by 2003. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990716.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
