<HEADLINE> India's Rice Exports Dip by 54 pct in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 16 (Xinhua) -- India's rice export registered a
sharp decline of over 50 percent during the first quarter of the
current 1999-2000 financial year on poor demand from major
importing nations, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Total registration for shipment of rice stood at 654,840 tons
as on July 2, down 54.55 percent from 1.278 million tons
registered for exports in the previous corresponding period last
year.
</P>
<P>
While 543,000 tons of non-basmati rice has been registered for
exports with the Agriculture and Processed Food Products Export
Development Authority (APEDA), 111,000 tons of basmati rice was
registered till July 2, APEDA sources said.
</P>
<P>
Industry sources said the sharp decline in rice exports was
mainly due to poor demand from Bangladesh, which was a major buyer
of Indian rice last year. 
</P>
