<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Army Expects More Recruits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The second phase of the Sri Lankan
army's recruitment drive this year will be held from August 9 to
30, a military spokesman said Friday.
</P>
<P>
"We need more troops to hold on to the vast tracts of newly
liberated areas," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
However, the spokesman declined to specify the number of
recruits.
</P>
<P>
Recruitment will take place at the army's recruitment center in
Colombo and at district secretariat offices and army camps located
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
In May, the army launched a recruitment drive in a bid to
recruit 10,000 men including minority Tamils, but no Tamils
responded to the drive for fear of Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan army, plagued by a high rate of desertion, has
said it needed at least 20,000 men to step up its war against the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting for a Tamil homeland for minority
Tamils in the north and east of the country since 1983. 
</P>
