<HEADLINE> China Expects Summer Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua)-- China is expected to reap a bigger
harvest for the summer season this year, up by more than five
million tons over the same period last year, said Ye Zhen,
spokesman of the National Bureau of Statistics today.
</P>
<P>
Last summer, China had a grain output of 113.1 billion kilos,
down 14.6 billion kilos from the previous year due to severe
floods.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's rapeseed output will also increase by more
than 15 percent to 1.4 million tons. Aquatic products and forestry
have also shown growth.
</P>
<P>
However, pork price has dropped sharply and the number of pigs
is shrinking, he noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
