<HEADLINE> Cisco Aids China in Spreading Networking Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The American Cisco System (China)
networking Technology Co. Ltd has launched a new institute on
networking technology in this northern China's municipality with
cooperation from the Tianjin University.
</P>
<P>
This is the 15th such institute the company has set up in China,
and indicated the company's active role in help consolidate the
networking technology of the nation's information industry.
</P>
<P>
As the leading enterprise in global networking technology,
Cisco provides more than 80 percent of the hardware and software
needed on Internet.
</P>
<P>
Cisco launched its global training project in October 1997 in
the wake of increasing number of professionals in networking
technology and backward education in that area, aiming to form a
global training system based on institutes on networking
technology. With intellectual and funding support from Cisco,
about 1,000 such institutes have been set up in 14 countries so
far.
</P>
<P>
China becomes a main target in Cisco's market development
strategy, and the company has started 15 such institutes in cities
including Shanghai, Beijing, Chengdu, Wuhan, Xi'an, and Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Also, Cisco started a branch company and four representative
offices in China, and played an active role in almost every large-
scale project in building the nation's information super-highway.
</P>
<P>
According to an executive of the Cisco company, over 90 high
schools and institutions of higher learning are expected to start
offering courses in networking technologies provided by Cisco by
the end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
