<HEADLINE> Urgent: Chinese Economy Grows 7.6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China's economy grew 7.6 percent
in the first half of this year, the National Bureau of Statistics
(NBS) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, the country achieved a total Gross
Domestic Product (GDP) of 3,618.9 billion yuan, said Ye Zhen,
spokesman of the NBS at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
