<HEADLINE> China's Exports Down, Imports Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China's total imports and exports
reached 158 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of this year,
up 4.4 percent over the same period last year, the National Bureau
of Statistics (NBS) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference, NBS spokesman NBS spokesman Ye
Zhen said that total exports in the past six months were 83
billion dollars, down 4.6 percent from the same period last year,
while imports soared 16.6 percent to hit 75 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
China's trade surplus was eight billion dollars during the
period, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months, the contracted volume of foreign
direct investment was 19.4 billion dollars, down 19.9 percent,
while the actually utilized foreign capital stood at 18.6 billion
dollars, down 9.2 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
