<HEADLINE> Argentina Requests Calmness in Face of Mercosur Trade Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Argentine ambassador to
Brazil, Jorge Herrer Vegas, said Thursday the increasing trade
conflicts between members of the South American Common Market (
Mercosur) were caused by protectionist measures and called for
calmness so as not to damage integration.
</P>
<P>
Argentina imposed tariffs on the import of cotton fibers and
tweed from Brazil and other countries Wednesday, triggering
complaints from its neighbors.
</P>
<P>
He urged partners of the regional economic bloc to keep calm
and try not to bring damage to the integrating process.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur groups Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay with
Chile and Bolivia as partners. 
</P>
