<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Fixed Assets Rises by 15.1 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- China's investment in fixed assets
increased by 15.1 percent to reach 668.7 billion yuan in the first
half of this year, according to a news conference held here today.
</P>
<P>
In the period, investment continues to incline to basic
industries and infrastructure facilities, according to Ye Zhen,
spokesman of the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The investment in farm, forestry, animal husbandry, fishery and
water conservancy is up 76.8 percent, its proportion in total
investment rises by 1.5 percentage points as compared with that in
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The investment in transportation, posts and telecommunications
is up 27 percent and its share rises by two percentage points,
said Ye. 
</P>
