<HEADLINE> Team USA to Play in Pre Olympic Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Team USA, comprising of nine
NBA stars and three lottery picks, is the overwhelming favorite to
win the Pre-Olympic Basketball Tournament of the Americas and
plays its first game tonight against Uruguay in San Juan, Puerto
Rico.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay upset Cuba 87-84 in overtime on Wednesday in the
opening day of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The United States has won 11 of 13 Olympics, including the last
two with star-studded NBA teams. This squad should do the same as
no country in the world can match these big Americans.
</P>
<P>
Ten teams from North, Central and South America are entered and
everyone else is playing for second place -- and the coveted
Olympic berth that comes with it. The teams reaching the gold
medal game on July 25 earn a spot in the draw for the 2000
Olympics in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Houston Rockets coach Rudy Tomjanovich was selected to coach
this team but withdrew due to exhaustion, leaving the duties to
Philadelphia 76ers coach Larry Brown. Brown's toughest task may be
finding minutes for 12 players, all of whom were selected 14th or
better in the NBA draft.
</P>
<P>
Team USA is led by San Antonio Spurs center-forward Tim Duncan,
who is coming off a Most Valuable Player showing in the NBA Finals.
He twisted an ankle in practice last week but is ready to go.
</P>
<P>
Joining Duncan in the frontcourt are forwards Kevin Garnett of
the Minnesota Timberwolves, Vin Baker of the Seattle SuperSonics
and Tom Gugliotta of the Phoenix Suns. The backcourt is extremely
deep, with point guards Gary Payton of Seattle, Jason Kidd of
Phoenix and Tim Hardaway of the Miami Heat. Allan Houston of the
New York Knicks and Steve Smith of the Atlanta Hawks are the
shooting guards.
</P>
<P>
The selected collegians are forward Elton Brand of the Chicago
Bulls, Wally Szczerbiak of Minnesota and Richard Hamilton of the
Washington Wizards.
</P>
<P>
The tournament is split into two groups of five teams. The USA
is in Group A and also will play Canada, Argentina and Cuba in the
preliminary round.
</P>
<P>
Group B consists of the Dominican Republic, Venezuela, Panama,
Brazil and Puerto Rico. The semi-finals are on July 24, with the
winners earning an Olympic berth and playing for the gold medal
one day later. 
</P>
