with the moving forward of the permanent status agreement," which
obviously was at odds with Clinton's intention. The president
hoped the Wye accord should be carried out immediately with the
revival of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
A senior U.S. official said after the first summit between
Clinton and Barak, "The president said that it was very clear that
this was a leader who was going to be scrupulous in terms of
fulfilling obligations and also very vigilant in terms of pursuing
peace with Israeli security in mind."
</P>
<P>
