<HEADLINE> Old Industrial Base Active in Economic Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, an old industrial base
in northeast China's Liaoning province, is expected to host a
series of economic exchange events as a move to further explore
its industrial advantage and potential.
</P>
<P>
To attract more overseas direct investment to the city,
Shenyang will host an auto industry exposition and an
international trade talks between September 2 and 6, which will
see participation of 150 domestic manufacturers of automobiles and
auto-parts, and world-renowned automobile makers such as the
General Motors from the United States, Mercedes-Benz from Germany,
and Toyota Motor from Japan.
</P>
<P>
So far, Shenyang has established trade links with businesses
from more than 100 countries and regions, half of which have
already set up joint ventures in the city.
</P>
<P>
The international trade talks, aimed at facilitate the opening-
up of Shenyang and other cities in central Liaoning, is expected
to introduce a list of projects in electronics, environment
industry, tourism and technology development to attract overseas
investors, and 18 Shenyang-based enterprises will also participate
in talks seeking overseas partners.
</P>
<P>
A special forum focusing on cooperation between Shenyang and
multinationals will be held between September 9 and 11. An experts
group is expected to be formed on the forum to do field studies on
the city and draft an implementation plan for such long-term and
effective cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A fair featuring exhibition of all sorts of commodities such as
daily necessities, clothing, and food will be held between October
28 and November 2, which is expected to enhance the city's role as
a center for commodities exchange.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city government is also planning a forum on
electrical power industry, and an exhibition on power technologies
and equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
