<DOCNO> XIE19990716.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Opposes U.S. Intervention in Latin America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Cuba firmly opposes any U.S.
intervention in any Latin American country, visiting Cuban Foreign
Minister Felipe Perez Roque said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference before ending his visit to
Panama, Perez Roque said his country rejects any intent of the
United States to maintain permanent presence in the Panamanian
territory.
</P>
<P>
He said Cuba also considers it crucial to search for a peaceful
settlement to Colombia's internal war, saying the current
situation there hinders the process of integration of Latin
America and the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
Colombia has been suffering from chaos of civil wars for a
decade. The Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC), the
country's top guerrilla group, clashed with the armed forces in
the past week near Santafe de Bogota, capital of the country. The
fighting was the biggest in 40 years, leaving hundreds of people
killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
