<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Guerrouj Pulles out of Nice and Paris Meetings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- World mile and 1500 meters record
holder Hicham El Guerrouj, who sustained a minor injury, has
pulled out of the Nice and Paris meetings over the next six days,
reports said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
But there was no details about his injuries announced. The
reports only said it was a complaint that also affected the
Moroccan middle distance runner last season.
</P>
<P>
He will instead return to Rabat for medical checks but should
be fit for the Seville world championships next month.
</P>
<P>
He has also withdrawn from next Wednesday's Paris Golden League
meeting at Charlety. 
</P>
