<HEADLINE> Japan Hopes to Host 2001 Copa America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 15 (Xinhuya) -- Japan has expressed the hope
to step in as the host of the 2001 Copa America if Colombia
renounces, the South American confederation said in Ciudad Del
Este, Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
However, CONMEBOL President Nicolas Leoz said he fully expected
the tournament to be held in Colombia as planned.
</P>
<P>
A recent wave of violence in Colombia has raised concern about
the country's ability to stage the biennial contintental nations
championship.
</P>
<P>
Japan, like Mexico, took part in the current Copa America as a
guest. The Asians were eliminated in the first round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
