<HEADLINE> Brazil's Industrial Production Falls 3.3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Of the country's 11 economic zones, 8 registered a production
growth, with the largest one in Rio de Janeiro (8.3 percent).
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, fallings of 8.6 percent in Sao Paulo, 5 in Minas
Gerais and 1.9 in Rio Grande knocked down the national average
growth percentage. The three states are the main ones in Brazilian
economy. 
</P>
