<HEADLINE> Road Accident Leaves 7 Dead in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Seven persons were killed and
two others seriously injured on Thursday when a Uruguayan van
collided with a Brazilian bus on Argentina's national highway 12.
</P>
<P>
According to a police report, the accident occurred at dawn in
the Ceibas locality of the Entre Rios province.
</P>
<P>
Seven passengers on the Uruguayan van died almost immediately,
and two others were rushed to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the tragedy was still under investigation.
