<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile to Renew Flights to Malvinas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Chile announced Thursday it will
renew flights to the Malvinas in mid-October following the
agreement made Wednesday between Argentina and Britain.
</P>
<P>
Chile suspended flights to the Malvinas in March in protest
against the detention of Chile's ex-leader Augusto Pinochet in
London on October 16 last year.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Britain and Argentina agreed on a package of
measures, including lifting a ban on Argentines visiting the
Malvinas islands, resumption of direct flights from Chile and
cooperation on fish preservation in the South Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
The pact marked the most significant thaw in relations between
the two nations since they went to war over the islands in 1982.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Foreign Minister Juan Gabriel Valdes told the press
that the renewal of flights from Chile to the Malvinas was a
gesture of solidarity with Argentina.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
