<HEADLINE> Ferdinand Re-signs for Hammers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Rio Ferdinand has signed a new
contract with West Ham that will tie him to the club until 2005.
</P>
<P>
The London club was adamant that it would not sell the England
center-back, despite rumoured approaches by Roma of Italy and
Spanish side Real Madrid.
</P>
<P>
Ferdinand, 20, had signed a seven year deal with West Ham last
year, but is understood to have agreed on an improved contract.
</P>
<P>
It seemed certain that he would stay at Upton Park after Roma
said on Wednesday that the deal to buy Ferdinand was "dead".
</P>
<P>
Reports in Italy said the Serie A side was prepared to pay 14
million pounds for the 20-year-old, with offers of a five-year
contract. 
