<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hughes Snubs Fulham </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League football
club Arsenal midfielder Stephen Hughes has turned down a four
million pounds move to First Division Fulham.
</P>
<P>
Left-sided Hughes, transfer listed after failing to force his
way above Marc Overmars and Emmanuel Petit in the Gunners pecking
order, had talks with Fulham boss Paul Bracewell but decided he
wanted to stay in the Premiership.
</P>
<P>
Hughes' agent Steve Kutner told the Daily Mail: "When he spoke
with Fulham they impressed him and the opportunity to play a part
in what they are trying to do was tempting.
</P>
<P>
"Paul Bracewell immediately won Stephen's respect with his
approach to the talks we had and we understood that this was an
opportunity where the benefits could have been mutual to club and
player.
</P>
<P>
"But his decision is based on the fact that he wants to remain
a Premiership footballer and is willing to wait until the talks we
are having with another couple of clubs in that division come to
fruition."
</P>
<P>
Liverpool, Aston Villa, West Ham, Tottenham, Middlesbrough,
Everton and Leeds have all been linked with 22-year-old Hughes.
</P>
</TEXT>
