<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchanges on
Thursday closed with the benchmark IPC index up 41.08 points, or 0.
7 percent, to 5,875.97 points.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 44.916 million shares for an amount of some
95.310 million U.S. dollars against 75.127 million shares worth
168.832 million dollars on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.45 to one dollar for
sale and 9.15 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico City, compared with 9.50 for sale and 9.15 for purchase on
the previous day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
