<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bolivia's The Strongest Lays-off Whole Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Bolivian soccer club The
Strongest on Thursday announced it had fired its entire team after
players staged a week-long strike to demand three months worth of
back wages, according to reports from La Paz, Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
The Strongest's President Jorge Sfeir said the players had
shown "lack of respect" when they did not attend a conciliatory
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Vidal Gonzalez, a representative for the more than 20 players
fired, said the only solution to the conflict was for them to
quickly get their salaries". 
</P>
</TEXT>
